I was in an accident last May because this happened. My truck needed $20,000 worth of repairs because I smashed into a bridge and had  no power to the brakes and couldn't steer. We called Chysler Canada and they said they never heard of this issue and now I'm reading this 9 months later. Bullshit! I went and financed a new car because I refuse to drive that piece of junk because I knew darn well something was wrong with it. I'm thankful my daughter and I didn't end up dead. I really hope others come forward. I can't be the only person this has happened to.

A similar accident happened to me but in a 2015 Durango. My SUV  was turned off yet surged forcefully up a steep incline into a concrete bollard in front of a drug store. $3800 damage and Chrysler won't cover it because "we haven't had any other similar complaints." A simple internet search will show you lots. Chalked my accident up to driver error. I even overheard the male representative say, "Yeah, woman driver error!" üò°

That's exactly what the called mine too. The insurance agent said she had to write human error to start the claim and they don't deal with anything that could have been a manufacture defect. She said that would be an entirely separate thing and done only on my part and not theirs. She said should I decide to go that route and get a lawyer to investigate to contact her with the information but that they are only there to start the claim process for repairs. I asked if they could pay to have the data pulled and she said they dont provide that and that it's on our part if we want it done. I told her I'd have it done because I know it's not human error and she said well to start the claim I'll just out human error. The company who repaired our truck took 4 months and handed it over looking like crap so we refused to drive it off their lot. We asked them to read the data and they said they did but didn't provide us with a reading and just said no lights came up to indicate anything was wrong with the engine. We then called Dodge Canada and they said they never heard of this happening. That was 9 months ago and now there's a recall describing exactly what happened. They can't possibly turn a blind eye? I really hope no one died from this recall because it was the scariest thing I've ever been through. I'm not sure what to enter in the Google search engine to find other people's experience but we are getting a lawyer to see if we have a case.

I will never again by anything from Chrysler Jeep as they don't stand behind their products.  I never even got an apology or anything.
